{"id":12699,"title":"A method of inducing global cerebral ischemia.","abstract":"The four-vessel occlusion (4-VO) method of global forebrain cerebral ischemia mimics the human clinical condition of cardiac arrest. It results in selective neuronal damage and is a useful experimental system to dissect underlying mechanisms behind ischemic phenomena such as the differential susceptibility of CA1 compared to the CA3 region of the hippocampus. It also provides a \"proof-of-principle\" system for testing out potential agents for neuroprotection. ","date":"2014-02-10","categories":"Animal Diseases","split":"train","url":"http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/24510859","annotations":[{"name":"Hippocampus","weight":0.889548,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Hippocampus"},{"name":"Heart","weight":0.756683,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Heart"},{"name":"Cerebrum","weight":0.750806,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cerebrum"},{"name":"Ischemia","weight":0.724397,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ischemia"},{"name":"Neuron","weight":0.71741,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Neuron"},{"name":"Forebrain","weight":0.661256,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Forebrain"},{"name":"Neuroprotection","weight":0.560932,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Neuroprotection"},{"name":"Human","weight":0.284114,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Human"},{"name":"Cardiac arrest","weight":0.23843,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cardiac_arrest"},{"name":"Brain ischemia","weight":0.164423,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Brain_ischemia"},{"name":"Hippocampus anatomy","weight":0.125945,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Hippocampus_anatomy"},{"name":"Dissection","weight":0.0629772,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Dissection"},{"name":"Clinical trial","weight":0.0562996,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.or